node.text:
Canada's breathtaking spots via @mthiessen. 🌈 Wanna see your pictures posted in our account? Apply for a feature on earthfever.net (link in my bio: @earthfever)

From natural landscapes to clean and modern cities, Canada is as picturesque as it gets when it comes to spectacular scenery. 🇨🇦

Swipe through and marvel at these incredible places! Save this post for reference when you visit Canada. 📝

@Nature Destinations in Canada
1-3. Niagara Falls, Ontario / New York, United States
4. Spirit Island, Alberta
5. Jasper, Alberta
6. Golden fields near Stony Plain, Alberta
7. Emerald Lake, British Columbia
8. Moraine Lake Road, Alberta
9. Lake Louise, Alberta
10. Edmonton, Alberta

Which one is your favorite? 👇

📸 @mthiessen
📍 Canada

node.text:
Welcome to paradise with @adrianbaias and @florina__toma 😍 Wanna see your pictures posted in our account? Apply for a feature on earthfever.net (link in my bio: @earthfever)

At Calilo, a tranquil retreat - a visionary conservation project that offers an escape from the clamour and the crowds. Think sun-drenched seclusion surrounded by an ancient olive-pricked landscape - @nature and art at its heart. Find yourself and all you need in a land in deep connection with everything.

Who would you share this hideout with? 😌

📽 @adrianbaias w/ @florina__toma

node.text:
In the eye of @nature with @jovi_travel 😍 Wanna see your pictures posted in our account? Apply for a feature on earthfever.net (link in my bio: @earthfever)

Would you dare to swim here? This incredible @nature spring in Croatia. 🇭🇷

This is a spring (outflow of groundwater) that is part of a hydrological system. And this is one of the sources of the Cetina River in southern Croatia. With depths of over 150 meters (490 feet) was explored by divers reaching 115 meters. No need to say, the abyss looks endless and scary.

📽 @jovi_travel 
📍 Cetina River Spring, Dalmatia, Croatia

node.text:
Would you ride this coaster? 💚 Share your photos with us and we will post them in our account. Apply for a feature following the link in our bio: @earthfever

Sliding through the forests of Borsec in Romania with @ivnicoara 🤪

The new Sunkid Mountain Coaster with its 1,440 metres is one of the longest summer toboggan runs Romania has to offer.

The small town of Borsec with its 2,500 residents is about 50 kilometres to the west of Durau. A popular spa in the times of the Royal and Imperial Monarchy, the place is currently developing an upwards trend. Since this summer, its guests are able to enjoy a new Sunkid Mountain Coaster as well. Tag someone you would share this experience with! 🤯

📽 @ivnicoara
📍 Mountain Coaster Borsec, Romania
🎶 Kaleo - Way Down We Go
